     9	
    10	# 12-TX Parity Matrix
    11	
    12	Snapshot taken at slice start of Phase 12-TX (TS → Python parity audit).
    13	Per `dev/design/bindings.md` § 1, the parity claim is "same five-verb
    14	canonical set + same error class taxonomy + same data shapes in
    15	language-idiomatic spelling". Cross-language idiom differences
    16	(`camelCase` vs `snake_case`; positional vs kwarg; `Promise` vs sync;
    17	options-object vs keyword-arg) are **intentional per
    18	`dev/interfaces/typescript.md` and `dev/interfaces/python.md`** and are
    19	recorded here as `📋 divergence-by-design`, **not** as gaps.
    20	
    21	Legend:
    22	
    23	- ✅ **parity-OK** — both surfaces present; spec-compliant idiom differences acknowledged
    24	- ❌ **gap** — TS missing what Python has, or vice versa, where the locked interface spec implies parity
    25	- 📋 **divergence-by-design** — locked spec explicitly diverges
    26	
    27	## 1. Five-verb canonical surface (REQ-053; AC-057a)
    28	
    29	| Verb                                             | Python (`src/python/fathomdb/`)                                          | TypeScript (`src/ts/src/`)                                                                     | Status                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
    30	| ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
    31	| `Engine.open`                                    | `Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` → `Engine`          | `Engine.open(path, options?)` → `Promise<Engine>`                                              | 📋 sync vs Promise; kwargs vs options-object; both per spec                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
    32	| `Engine.open` return: **structured open report** | NOT returned (PyO3 binding drops `OpenedEngine.report`)                  | NOT returned (napi binding drops `OpenedEngine.report`)                                        | ⚠️ **0.6.0 documented gap** — locked specs (interfaces/python.md L25-28, interfaces/typescript.md L27-29) call for "engine handle plus structured open report owned by design/engine.md". Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report: OpenReport }` (engine src L541-553), but both bindings currently surface only the engine. Symmetric parity (both bindings drop it); not a TS-vs-Python gap. **Resolution:** implementation deferred to **0.6.1** as a follow-up slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT. Release notes disclose the gap; clients depending on migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage report wait for 0.6.1. Spec text in interfaces/{python,typescript}.md amended to add "0.6.0 caveat" note. |
    33	| `engine.write`                                   | `engine.write(batch=None)` → `WriteReceipt` (sync)                       | `engine.write(batch=[])` → `Promise<WriteReceipt>`                                             | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
    34	| `engine.search`                                  | `engine.search(query)` → `SearchResult` (sync)                           | `engine.search(query)` → `Promise<SearchResult>`                                               | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
    35	| `engine.close`                                   | `engine.close()` → `None` (sync)                                         | `engine.close()` → `Promise<void>`                                                             | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
    36	| `admin.configure`                                | `admin.configure(engine, *, name, body)` → `WriteReceipt` (module-level) | `admin.configure(engine, { name, body })` → `Promise<WriteReceipt>` (object-literal namespace) | ✅                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
    37	
    38	## 2. Engine-attached instrumentation / control
    39	
    40	| Method                  | Python                                                                             | TypeScript                                                    | Status                                                                                                                                     |
    41	| ----------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
    42	| `drain`                 | `engine.drain(*, timeout_s: float\|int = 0)` (sync)                                | `engine.drain(timeoutMs: number)` → `Promise<void>`           | 📋 timeout unit (seconds vs ms) + sync vs Promise per spec                                                                                 |
    43	| `counters`              | `engine.counters()` → `CounterSnapshot` (empty dataclass; **drops** native fields) | `engine.counters()` → `CounterSnapshot` (6 fields populated)  | ❌ **gap closed in 12-TX**: Python wrapper threw away the 6 fields the PyO3 layer already returns                                          |
    44	| `set_profiling`         | `engine.set_profiling(*, enabled)`                                                 | `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`                                | 📋 kwarg vs positional per spec                                                                                                            |
    45	| `set_slow_threshold_ms` | `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(*, value)`                                           | `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`                            | 📋 kwarg vs positional per spec                                                                                                            |
    46	| Subscriber attach       | `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`          | `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })` | 📋 logging.Logger vs callback per `interfaces/python.md` § 51 + `interfaces/typescript.md` § 54 (explicitly different host-adapter shapes) |
    47	
    48	## 3. Caller-visible data shapes
    49	
    50	| Shape             | Python field set                                                                                                                             | TypeScript field set                                                                  | Status                                                                                     |
    51	| ----------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
    52	| `WriteReceipt`    | `cursor: int`                                                                                                                                | `cursor: number`                                                                      | ✅                                                                                         |
    53	| `SoftFallback`    | `branch: Literal["vector","text"]`                                                                                                           | `branch: "vector" \| "text"`                                                          | ✅                                                                                         |
    54	| `SearchResult`    | `projection_cursor: int`, `soft_fallback: SoftFallback \| None`, `results: list[str]`                                                        | `projectionCursor: number`, `softFallback: SoftFallback \| null`, `results: string[]` | ✅ (casing)                                                                                |
    55	| `CounterSnapshot` | _(was: empty dataclass)_; **after 12-TX**: `queries`, `writes`, `write_rows`, `admin_ops`, `cache_hit`, `cache_miss` (all `int`)             | `queries`, `writes`, `writeRows`, `adminOps`, `cacheHit`, `cacheMiss` (all `number`)  | ❌ → ✅ (gap closed; 6 fields added to Python dataclass + wired through `Engine.counters`) |
    56	| `EngineConfig`    | `embedder_pool_size`, `scheduler_runtime_threads`, `provenance_row_cap`, `embedder_call_timeout_ms`, `slow_threshold_ms` (all `int \| None`) | same five knobs, `Optional<number>`, camelCase                                        | ✅                                                                                         |
    57	
    58	## 4. Error-class taxonomy (15+ leaves per `dev/design/errors.md`)
    59	
    60	Python defines a root `EngineError` plus 18 concrete leaves. TypeScript
    61	defines `FathomDbError` plus 18 concrete leaves. Both bindings expose
    62	1:1 the same leaf set:
