dev/plans/runs/C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-20260504T022727Z.log:90:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X8XouwDzC6EVPjwXzSs7jS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Rust Public Interface\n3\tdate: 2026-04-24\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Public Rust surface (traits, functions, types, errors) for 0.6.0\n6\tblast_radius: src/rust/crates/fathomdb; design/engine.md; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# Rust Interface\n11\t\n12\tThis file owns Rust-visible symbol spelling and result shape. Cross-binding\n13\tparity rules remain owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n14\t\n15\t## Support posture\n16\t\n17\tThe Rust facade is stable public Rust contract in 0.6.0 and is the\n18\tground-truth source for engine-side type names. It is not part of the\n19\tPython/TypeScript five-verb SDK parity set tested by AC-057a; Rust keeps the\n20\tfacade shape below unless a successor ADR expands it.\n21\t\n22\t## Public surface\n23\t\n24\tRust exposes:\n25\t\n26\t- `Engine::open(...) -> Result<OpenedEngine, EngineOpenError>`\n27\t- `Engine::write(...) -> Result<WriteReceipt, EngineError>`\n28\t- `Engine::search(...) -> Result<SearchResult, EngineError>`\n29\t- `Engine::close(...) -> Result<(), EngineError>`\n30\t\n31\t`OpenedEngine` contains:\n32\t\n33\t- `engine`\n34\t- `report`\n35\t\n36\t`report` is the `OpenReport` owned by `design/engine.md`.\n37\t\n38\t## Engine-attached instrumentation / control methods\n39\t\n40\tThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n41\t\n42\t- `Engine::drain(timeout_ms: u64) -> Result<(), EngineError>`\n43\t- `Engine::counters() -> CounterSnapshot`\n44\t- `Engine::set_profiling(enabled: bool) -> Result<(), EngineError>`\n45\t- `Engine::set_slow_threshold_ms(value: u64) -> Result<(), EngineError>`\n46\t- `Engine::subscribe(&self, subscriber: Arc<dyn lifecycle::Subscriber>) -> Subscription`\n47\t\n48\t`drain` is a bounded completion surface for post-commit projection work. It\n49\treturns `Ok(())` when the engine-owned background projection queue reaches a\n50\tquiescent state before `timeout_ms`, and returns a typed runtime error when the\n51\ttimeout elapses first.\n52\t\n53\t`subscribe` owns host-subscriber attachment and may carry heartbeat-cadence\n54\toptions. The payload semantics remain owned by `design/lifecycle.md` and\n55\t`design/migrations.md`.\n56\t\n57\t## Companion embedder contract\n58\t\n59\tThe Rust workspace also exposes the semver-stable companion crate\n60\t`fathomdb-embedder-api` for engine-owned embedder dispatch:\n61\t\n62\t- `Embedder`\n63\t- `EmbedderIdentity { name, revision, dimension }`\n64\t- `EmbedderError`\n65\t\n66\t## Caller-visible data shapes\n67\t\n68\t- `WriteReceipt` has exactly one public field: `cursor`\n69\t- `SearchResult` exposes `projection_cursor`, which names the terminal\n70\t  projection-visible point for the search snapshot\n71\t- hybrid fallback, when present, exposes a typed branch enum whose values are\n72\t  owned by `design/retrieval.md`\n73\t- counter/profile/stress payload shapes are owned by `design/lifecycle.md`\n74\t\n75\t## Errors\n76\t\n77\tRust exposes typed open/runtime errors without message parsing:\n78\t\n79\t- `EngineOpenError`\n80\t- `EngineError`\n81\t\n82\tCanonical leaf mapping lives in `design/errors.md`. This file adopts those\n83\ttypes without renaming them.\n84\t\n85\t## Non-presence\n86\t\n87\tThe Rust runtime surface does not expose recovery verbs. Recovery remains CLI\n88\tonly per `design/recovery.md` and `design/bindings.md`.\n89\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8996a1e6-f0cf-41f6-bd76-ad56a5a9b42e","uuid":"c7c97e00-0589-4048-92b2-4b547c380221","timestamp":"2026-05-04T02:27:37.333Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-pack5-C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-20260504T022727Z/dev/interfaces/rust.md","content":"---\ntitle: Rust Public Interface\ndate: 2026-04-24\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Public Rust surface (traits, functions, types, errors) for 0.6.0\nblast_radius: src/rust/crates/fathomdb; design/engine.md; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# Rust Interface\n\nThis file owns Rust-visible symbol spelling and result shape. Cross-binding\nparity rules remain owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Support posture\n\nThe Rust facade is stable public Rust contract in 0.6.0 and is the\nground-truth source for engine-side type names. It is not part of the\nPython/TypeScript five-verb SDK parity set tested by AC-057a; Rust keeps the\nfacade shape below unless a successor ADR expands it.\n\n## Public surface\n\nRust exposes:\n\n- `Engine::open(...) -> Result<OpenedEngine, EngineOpenError>`\n- `Engine::write(...) -> Result<WriteReceipt, EngineError>`\n- `Engine::search(...) -> Result<SearchResult, EngineError>`\n- `Engine::close(...) -> Result<(), EngineError>`\n\n`OpenedEngine` contains:\n\n- `engine`\n- `report`\n\n`report` is the `OpenReport` owned by `design/engine.md`.\n\n## Engine-attached instrumentation / control methods\n\nThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n\n- `Engine::drain(timeout_ms: u64) -> Result<(), EngineError>`\n- `Engine::counters() -> CounterSnapshot`\n- `Engine::set_profiling(enabled: bool) -> Result<(), EngineError>`\n- `Engine::set_slow_threshold_ms(value: u64) -> Result<(), EngineError>`\n- `Engine::subscribe(&self, subscriber: Arc<dyn lifecycle::Subscriber>) -> Subscription`\n\n`drain` is a bounded completion surface for post-commit projection work. It\nreturns `Ok(())` when the engine-owned background projection queue reaches a\nquiescent state before `timeout_ms`, and returns a typed runtime error when the\ntimeout elapses first.\n\n`subscribe` owns host-subscriber attachment and may carry heartbeat-cadence\noptions. The payload semantics remain owned by `design/lifecycle.md` and\n`design/migrations.md`.\n\n## Companion embedder contract\n\nThe Rust workspace also exposes the semver-stable companion crate\n`fathomdb-embedder-api` for engine-owned embedder dispatch:\n\n- `Embedder`\n- `EmbedderIdentity { name, revision, dimension }`\n- `EmbedderError`\n\n## Caller-visible data shapes\n\n- `WriteReceipt` has exactly one public field: `cursor`\n- `SearchResult` exposes `projection_cursor`, which names the terminal\n  projection-visible point for the search snapshot\n- hybrid fallback, when present, exposes a typed branch enum whose values are\n  owned by `design/retrieval.md`\n- counter/profile/stress payload shapes are owned by `design/lifecycle.md`\n\n## Errors\n\nRust exposes typed open/runtime errors without message parsing:\n\n- `EngineOpenError`\n- `EngineError`\n\nCanonical leaf mapping lives in `design/errors.md`. This file adopts those\ntypes without renaming them.\n\n## Non-presence\n\nThe Rust runtime surface does not expose recovery verbs. Recovery remains CLI\nonly per `design/recovery.md` and `design/bindings.md`.\n","numLines":89,"startLine":1,"totalLines":89}}}
dev/plans/runs/C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-20260504T022727Z.log:248:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019nKHXAPMWv97TSRrtCSc69","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tpub mod lifecycle;\n2\t\n3\tuse std::collections::{BTreeMap, BTreeSet, VecDeque};\n4\tuse std::error::Error;\n5\tuse std::fmt::{Display, Formatter};\n6\tuse std::fs::{File, OpenOptions};\n7\tuse std::io::{Seek, SeekFrom, Write};\n8\tuse std::path::{Path, PathBuf};\n9\tuse std::sync::atomic::{AtomicBool, AtomicU64, Ordering};\n10\tuse std::sync::Once;\n11\tuse std::sync::{Arc, Condvar, Mutex};\n12\tuse std::thread::{self, JoinHandle};\n13\tuse std::time::{Duration, Instant};\n14\t\n15\tuse fathomdb_embedder_api::{Embedder, EmbedderError as RuntimeEmbedderError, EmbedderIdentity};\n16\tuse fathomdb_query::compile_text_query;\n17\tuse fathomdb_schema::{\n18\t    migrate_with_event_sink, MigrationError as SchemaMigrationError, MigrationStepReport,\n19\t    LOCK_SUFFIX, MIGRATIONS, SCHEMA_VERSION,\n20\t};\n21\tuse jsonschema::JSONSchema;\n22\tuse rusqlite::{params, Connection};\n23\tuse serde_json::Value;\n24\tuse sqlite_vec::sqlite3_vec_init;\n25\t\n26\t#[cfg(unix)]\n27\tuse std::os::unix::fs::OpenOptionsExt;\n28\t\n29\tconst DEFAULT_EMBEDDER_NAME: &str = \"fathomdb-noop\";\n30\tconst DEFAULT_EMBEDDER_REVISION: &str = \"0.6.0-scaffold\";\n31\tconst DEFAULT_EMBEDDER_DIMENSION: u32 = 384;\n32\t\n33\t/// REQ-006a / AC-007a default slow-statement threshold. Mutated at runtime\n34\t/// via [`Engine::set_slow_threshold_ms`].\n35\tconst DEFAULT_SLOW_THRESHOLD_MS: u64 = 100;\n36\tconst DEFAULT_VECTOR_PROFILE: &str = \"default\";\n37\tconst DEFAULT_VECTOR_PARTITION: &str = \"vector_default\";\n38\tconst DEFAULT_PROVENANCE_ROW_CAP: u64 = 1_000_000;\n39\tconst PROJECTION_CURSOR_KEY: &str = \"projection_cursor\";\n40\tconst PROJECTION_WORKERS: usize = 2;\n41\tconst PROJECTION_INFLIGHT_LIMIT: usize = PROJECTION_WORKERS * 4;\n42\tconst PROJECTION_COMMIT_BATCH: usize = 16;\n43\tconst DEFAULT_PROJECTION_RETRY_DELAYS_MS: [u64; 3] = [1_000, 4_000, 16_000];\n44\t\n45\t/// Reader pool size. Per `dev/design/engine.md` § Writer / reader split,\n46\t/// reader connections are pooled and never serialize behind one\n47\t/// connection. AC-021 exercises 8 concurrent readers.\n48\tconst READER_POOL_SIZE: usize = 8;\n49\t\n50\tpub struct Engine {\n51\t    path: PathBuf,\n52\t    next_cursor: AtomicU64,\n53\t    closed: AtomicBool,\n54\t    lock: Mutex<Option<File>>,\n55\t    connection: Mutex<Option<Connection>>,\n56\t    reader_pool: ReaderPool,\n57\t    counters: lifecycle::Counters,\n58\t    subscribers: Arc<lifecycle::SubscriberRegistry>,\n59\t    profiling_enabled: Arc<AtomicBool>,\n60\t    slow_threshold_ms: Arc<AtomicU64>,\n61\t    runtime_embedder: Option<Arc<dyn Embedder>>,\n62\t    runtime_embedder_identity: EmbedderIdentity,\n63\t    projection_runtime: ProjectionRuntime,\n64\t    provenance_row_cap: AtomicU64,\n65\t    /// Per-connection profile-callback contexts. Each box's pointer is\n66\t    /// installed into the connection's `sqlite3_profile` userdata; the\n67\t    /// box must outlive the connection so the callback never reads\n68\t    /// freed memory. Connections are dropped before this vec on\n69\t    /// `close`/`Drop`, so the lifetime ordering holds.\n70\t    ///\n71\t    /// Why `Box<ProfileContext>` and not `ProfileContext` directly: the\n72\t    /// FFI pointer captured during `install_profile_callback` MUST\n73\t    /// remain stable for the connection's lifetime; pushing onto a\n74\t    /// `Vec<ProfileContext>` could reallocate and invalidate that\n75\t    /// pointer.\n76\t    #[allow(clippy::vec_box)]\n77\t    profile_contexts: Mutex<Vec<Box<ProfileContext>>>,\n78\t    #[cfg(debug_assertions)]\n79\t    force_next_commit_failure: AtomicBool,\n80\t}\n81\t\n82\t#[derive(Clone, Debug)]\n83\tstruct ProjectionJob {\n84\t    cursor: u64,\n85\t    kind: String,\n86\t    body: String,\n87\t}\n88\t\n89\t#[derive(Debug, Default)]\n90\tstruct ProjectionRuntimeState {\n91\t    active_jobs: usize,\n92\t    queued_jobs: usize,\n93\t    frozen: bool,\n94\t    pending_scan: bool,\n95\t    stopping: bool,\n96\t    in_flight: BTreeSet<u64>,\n97\t}\n98\t\n99\tstruct ProjectionRuntimeShared {\n100\t    path: PathBuf,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8996a1e6-f0cf-41f6-bd76-ad56a5a9b42e","uuid":"570d9736-a1c9-4005-81b3-e7112dc29dd0","timestamp":"2026-05-04T02:27:49.151Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-pack5-C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-20260504T022727Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs","content":"pub mod lifecycle;\n\nuse std::collections::{BTreeMap, BTreeSet, VecDeque};\nuse std::error::Error;\nuse std::fmt::{Display, Formatter};\nuse std::fs::{File, OpenOptions};\nuse std::io::{Seek, SeekFrom, Write};\nuse std::path::{Path, PathBuf};\nuse std::sync::atomic::{AtomicBool, AtomicU64, Ordering};\nuse std::sync::Once;\nuse std::sync::{Arc, Condvar, Mutex};\nuse std::thread::{self, JoinHandle};\nuse std::time::{Duration, Instant};\n\nuse fathomdb_embedder_api::{Embedder, EmbedderError as RuntimeEmbedderError, EmbedderIdentity};\nuse fathomdb_query::compile_text_query;\nuse fathomdb_schema::{\n    migrate_with_event_sink, MigrationError as SchemaMigrationError, MigrationStepReport,\n    LOCK_SUFFIX, MIGRATIONS, SCHEMA_VERSION,\n};\nuse jsonschema::JSONSchema;\nuse rusqlite::{params, Connection};\nuse serde_json::Value;\nuse sqlite_vec::sqlite3_vec_init;\n\n#[cfg(unix)]\nuse std::os::unix::fs::OpenOptionsExt;\n\nconst DEFAULT_EMBEDDER_NAME: &str = \"fathomdb-noop\";\nconst DEFAULT_EMBEDDER_REVISION: &str = \"0.6.0-scaffold\";\nconst DEFAULT_EMBEDDER_DIMENSION: u32 = 384;\n\n/// REQ-006a / AC-007a default slow-statement threshold. Mutated at runtime\n/// via [`Engine::set_slow_threshold_ms`].\nconst DEFAULT_SLOW_THRESHOLD_MS: u64 = 100;\nconst DEFAULT_VECTOR_PROFILE: &str = \"default\";\nconst DEFAULT_VECTOR_PARTITION: &str = \"vector_default\";\nconst DEFAULT_PROVENANCE_ROW_CAP: u64 = 1_000_000;\nconst PROJECTION_CURSOR_KEY: &str = \"projection_cursor\";\nconst PROJECTION_WORKERS: usize = 2;\nconst PROJECTION_INFLIGHT_LIMIT: usize = PROJECTION_WORKERS * 4;\nconst PROJECTION_COMMIT_BATCH: usize = 16;\nconst DEFAULT_PROJECTION_RETRY_DELAYS_MS: [u64; 3] = [1_000, 4_000, 16_000];\n\n/// Reader pool size. Per `dev/design/engine.md` § Writer / reader split,\n/// reader connections are pooled and never serialize behind one\n/// connection. AC-021 exercises 8 concurrent readers.\nconst READER_POOL_SIZE: usize = 8;\n\npub struct Engine {\n    path: PathBuf,\n    next_cursor: AtomicU64,\n    closed: AtomicBool,\n    lock: Mutex<Option<File>>,\n    connection: Mutex<Option<Connection>>,\n    reader_pool: ReaderPool,\n    counters: lifecycle::Counters,\n    subscribers: Arc<lifecycle::SubscriberRegistry>,\n    profiling_enabled: Arc<AtomicBool>,\n    slow_threshold_ms: Arc<AtomicU64>,\n    runtime_embedder: Option<Arc<dyn Embedder>>,\n    runtime_embedder_identity: EmbedderIdentity,\n    projection_runtime: ProjectionRuntime,\n    provenance_row_cap: AtomicU64,\n    /// Per-connection profile-callback contexts. Each box's pointer is\n    /// installed into the connection's `sqlite3_profile` userdata; the\n    /// box must outlive the connection so the callback never reads\n    /// freed memory. Connections are dropped before this vec on\n    /// `close`/`Drop`, so the lifetime ordering holds.\n    ///\n    /// Why `Box<ProfileContext>` and not `ProfileContext` directly: the\n    /// FFI pointer captured during `install_profile_callback` MUST\n    /// remain stable for the connection's lifetime; pushing onto a\n    /// `Vec<ProfileContext>` could reallocate and invalidate that\n    /// pointer.\n    #[allow(clippy::vec_box)]\n    profile_contexts: Mutex<Vec<Box<ProfileContext>>>,\n    #[cfg(debug_assertions)]\n    force_next_commit_failure: AtomicBool,\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone, Debug)]\nstruct ProjectionJob {\n    cursor: u64,\n    kind: String,\n    body: String,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Default)]\nstruct ProjectionRuntimeState {\n    active_jobs: usize,\n    queued_jobs: usize,\n    frozen: bool,\n    pending_scan: bool,\n    stopping: bool,\n    in_flight: BTreeSet<u64>,\n}\n\nstruct ProjectionRuntimeShared {\n    path: PathBuf,","numLines":100,"startLine":1,"totalLines":2511}}}
