dev/plans/runs/12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z.log:74:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JHYmHV5TftB74GaVAAJgGk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# 0.6.0 Release Notes (Preview)\n2\t\n3\t**Status: pre-release.** `0.6.0` is on the `0.6.0-rewrite` branch\n4\tand has not yet been published to crates.io / PyPI / npm. This\n5\tpage previews what 0.6.0 will deliver when the GA tag fires.\n6\t\n7\t## What 0.6.0 delivers\n8\t\n9\t### Engine + storage substrate\n10\t\n11\t- Local-first retrieval engine on SQLite (FTS5 + `sqlite-vec`).\n12\t- Canonical writes, vector projections, scheduler, op-store,\n13\t  reader pool with thread-affine workers.\n14\t- Typed error hierarchy: `EngineError` plus structured leaves\n15\t  (`StorageError`, `ProjectionError`, `VectorError`,\n16\t  `EmbedderError`, `EmbedderNotConfiguredError`,\n17\t  `KindNotVectorIndexedError`, `SchedulerError`, `OpStoreError`,\n18\t  `WriteValidationError`, `SchemaValidationError`,\n19\t  `OverloadedError`, `ClosingError`, `DatabaseLockedError`,\n20\t  `CorruptionError`, `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`).\n21\t- Five-verb runtime SDK surface: `Engine.open`, `engine.write`,\n22\t  `engine.search`, `engine.close`, `admin.configure`.\n23\t- Engine-attached instrumentation: `engine.drain`,\n24\t  `engine.counters`, `engine.set_profiling`,\n25\t  `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms`, host logging subscriber attach.\n26\t\n27\t### Bindings\n28\t\n29\t- **Python SDK** (`fathomdb`) — PyO3 binding. Type stubs at\n30\t  `fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi`. Public surface locked at\n31\t  `dev/interfaces/python.md` (internal spec).\n32\t- **TypeScript SDK** (`fathomdb`) — napi-rs binding. Promise API,\n33\t  handoff pool, typed exception envelope.\n34\t- **Rust facade crate** (`fathomdb`) — re-exports the runtime\n35\t  verbs from `fathomdb-engine` for downstream Rust consumers.\n36\t- **CLI** (`fathomdb-cli`) — `doctor` and `recover` verbs\n37\t  (Phase 10a). Logical-id verbs deferred to 0.7.x — see below.\n38\t\n39\t### Release engineering\n40\t\n41\t- Two-axis versioning: Axis W (workspace lockstep across the\n42\t  six runtime/binding/CLI crates + Python + TS packages); Axis E\n43\t  (`fathomdb-embedder-api` independent — trait surface stability\n44\t  per ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol).\n45\t- 8-tier topological publish order via `.github/workflows/release.yml`\n46\t  with crates.io index-propagation sleeps between tiers and\n47\t  post-publish smoke against fresh installs from each registry.\n48\t- Single brand: `fathomdb` on crates.io / PyPI / npm.\n49\t- `scripts/set-version.sh --check-files` enforces axis lockstep\n50\t  pre-publish; pre-push hook runs the check before agent-verify.\n51\t- actionlint v1.7.7 wired as canonical workflow validator.\n52\t\n53\t## What is deferred (will not ship in 0.6.0 GA)\n54\t\n55\tThese are documented and will appear in the final GA release\n56\tnotes verbatim.\n57\t\n58\t### Performance gates (4 ACs)\n59\t\n60\tPerformance acceptance criteria **AC-012**, **AC-013**, **AC-019**,\n61\t**AC-020** are deferred for 0.6.0 (HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17\n62\tper Phase 12-P decision). Engine surfaces them as documented gates,\n63\tnot weakened ones. See `dev/test-plan.md` § Current Perf Attribution\n64\tfor the canonical rationale and Pack 7 remediation track.\n65\t\n66\t- **AC-012** text query latency on FTS5 (p50 ≤ 20 ms / p99 ≤ 150 ms):\n67\t  closes in **0.6.1** via canonical-runner re-measurement (dev\n68\t  runner is aarch64 Tegra ~3× slower than canonical x86_64). No\n69\t  engine code change expected.\n70\t- **AC-013** vector retrieval latency (p50 ≤ 50 ms / p99 ≤ 200 ms):\n71\t  closes via **Pack 7** batched-insert vec0 API (current bulk-seed\n72\t  is engine-surface gap, not retrieval-path issue).\n73\t- **AC-019** mixed-retrieval stress tail: closes via Pack 7\n74\t  (inherits AC-013 substrate).\n75\t- **AC-020** N=8 concurrent reader scaling: **architectural gap**.\n76\t  Best speedup on dev runner 3.53× vs required ≥ 5.33×; residual\n77\t  is `pcache1` mutex acquires on every page-fetch (hit-path).\n78\t  Closure requires Pack 7 vendor-SQLite work\n79\t  (`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` custom allocator OR WAL2 OR\n80\t  reader/writer physical separation OR vendor-SQLite swap). Pack\n81\t  5 + Pack 6 + Pack 6.G falsified every canonical-SQLite lever\n82\t  measurable on the AC-020 fixture.\n83\t\n84\t### `Engine.open` structured open report\n85\t\n86\tBoth Python and TypeScript SDKs currently return only the engine handle\n87\tfrom `Engine.open`. The structured open report (migration-version-\n88\treached, embedder-identity-confirmed, open-stage data) defined in\n89\t`design/engine.md` and called for by `interfaces/{python,typescript}.md`\n90\tis populated on the native Rust side (`OpenedEngine.report`) but\n91\t**dropped by both bindings in 0.6.0**.\n92\t\n93\tSurfacing the open report defers to **0.6.1** (slice\n94\t`12-TX-OPENREPORT`). Symmetric across both bindings, so not a\n95\tTS-vs-Python parity gap. Clients depending on open-report data\n96\tshould pin to 0.6.1 when it ships.\n97\t\n98\t### Logical-id verbs\n99\t\n100\t`purge_logical_id` and `restore_logical_id` deferred to **0.7.x**\n101\t(HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17 per Phase 12-V-VERBS decision). The\n102\tcanonical-identity substrate (`row_id` / `logical_id` /\n103\t`superseded_at` / `restore_provenance` columns, partial unique\n104\tindex on `(logical_id, kind)`, writer supersession step) is\n105\tdesign-only in 0.6.0 — verbs cannot be built without the substrate.\n106\t\n107\t**Client workaround for 0.6.0**: bulk-delete by source uses\n108\t`fathomdb recover --excise-source <id>` (landed in Phase 10a).\n109\tRestore-from-log workflows wait for 0.7.x.\n110\t\n111\tSee `dev/design/recovery.md` § Logical-id purge and restore for\n112\tthe design + substrate spec.\n113\t\n114\t### TypeScript SDK parity\n115\t\n116\t- TS milestone 1 shipped 2026-04-07; not yet feature-equal with\n117\t  Python. TS Python-parity is a Phase 12 deliverable (will close\n118\t  before GA tag) but lands after performance + security + verb\n119\t  decisions. Until then, prefer the Python SDK for production\n120\t  pilots.\n121\t\n122\t### Compatibility\n123\t\n124\t- **No 0.5.x compatibility shims or migrations.** 0.6.0 is a\n125\t  rewrite; clients on 0.5.x must follow a separate migration\n126\t  guide (not provided in 0.6.0).\n127\t\n128\t## How to follow along\n129\t\n130\t- Plan + status: `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` § Path to\n131\t  Client-Ready (0.6.0 GA).\n132\t- Public interface specs (internal-facing):\n133\t  `dev/interfaces/{rust,python,typescript,cli,wire}.md`.\n134\t- Acceptance scoreboard: `dev/acceptance.md`.\n135\t\n136\tWhen 0.6.0 GA tags, this page will be replaced with the final\n137\trelease notes including install commands for all three registries.\n138\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"f57c934a-054f-4572-a5c7-63ed1a765f0f","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:13.252Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/docs/release-notes/0.6.0.md","content":"# 0.6.0 Release Notes (Preview)\n\n**Status: pre-release.** `0.6.0` is on the `0.6.0-rewrite` branch\nand has not yet been published to crates.io / PyPI / npm. This\npage previews what 0.6.0 will deliver when the GA tag fires.\n\n## What 0.6.0 delivers\n\n### Engine + storage substrate\n\n- Local-first retrieval engine on SQLite (FTS5 + `sqlite-vec`).\n- Canonical writes, vector projections, scheduler, op-store,\n  reader pool with thread-affine workers.\n- Typed error hierarchy: `EngineError` plus structured leaves\n  (`StorageError`, `ProjectionError`, `VectorError`,\n  `EmbedderError`, `EmbedderNotConfiguredError`,\n  `KindNotVectorIndexedError`, `SchedulerError`, `OpStoreError`,\n  `WriteValidationError`, `SchemaValidationError`,\n  `OverloadedError`, `ClosingError`, `DatabaseLockedError`,\n  `CorruptionError`, `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`).\n- Five-verb runtime SDK surface: `Engine.open`, `engine.write`,\n  `engine.search`, `engine.close`, `admin.configure`.\n- Engine-attached instrumentation: `engine.drain`,\n  `engine.counters`, `engine.set_profiling`,\n  `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms`, host logging subscriber attach.\n\n### Bindings\n\n- **Python SDK** (`fathomdb`) — PyO3 binding. Type stubs at\n  `fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi`. Public surface locked at\n  `dev/interfaces/python.md` (internal spec).\n- **TypeScript SDK** (`fathomdb`) — napi-rs binding. Promise API,\n  handoff pool, typed exception envelope.\n- **Rust facade crate** (`fathomdb`) — re-exports the runtime\n  verbs from `fathomdb-engine` for downstream Rust consumers.\n- **CLI** (`fathomdb-cli`) — `doctor` and `recover` verbs\n  (Phase 10a). Logical-id verbs deferred to 0.7.x — see below.\n\n### Release engineering\n\n- Two-axis versioning: Axis W (workspace lockstep across the\n  six runtime/binding/CLI crates + Python + TS packages); Axis E\n  (`fathomdb-embedder-api` independent — trait surface stability\n  per ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol).\n- 8-tier topological publish order via `.github/workflows/release.yml`\n  with crates.io index-propagation sleeps between tiers and\n  post-publish smoke against fresh installs from each registry.\n- Single brand: `fathomdb` on crates.io / PyPI / npm.\n- `scripts/set-version.sh --check-files` enforces axis lockstep\n  pre-publish; pre-push hook runs the check before agent-verify.\n- actionlint v1.7.7 wired as canonical workflow validator.\n\n## What is deferred (will not ship in 0.6.0 GA)\n\nThese are documented and will appear in the final GA release\nnotes verbatim.\n\n### Performance gates (4 ACs)\n\nPerformance acceptance criteria **AC-012**, **AC-013**, **AC-019**,\n**AC-020** are deferred for 0.6.0 (HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17\nper Phase 12-P decision). Engine surfaces them as documented gates,\nnot weakened ones. See `dev/test-plan.md` § Current Perf Attribution\nfor the canonical rationale and Pack 7 remediation track.\n\n- **AC-012** text query latency on FTS5 (p50 ≤ 20 ms / p99 ≤ 150 ms):\n  closes in **0.6.1** via canonical-runner re-measurement (dev\n  runner is aarch64 Tegra ~3× slower than canonical x86_64). No\n  engine code change expected.\n- **AC-013** vector retrieval latency (p50 ≤ 50 ms / p99 ≤ 200 ms):\n  closes via **Pack 7** batched-insert vec0 API (current bulk-seed\n  is engine-surface gap, not retrieval-path issue).\n- **AC-019** mixed-retrieval stress tail: closes via Pack 7\n  (inherits AC-013 substrate).\n- **AC-020** N=8 concurrent reader scaling: **architectural gap**.\n  Best speedup on dev runner 3.53× vs required ≥ 5.33×; residual\n  is `pcache1` mutex acquires on every page-fetch (hit-path).\n  Closure requires Pack 7 vendor-SQLite work\n  (`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` custom allocator OR WAL2 OR\n  reader/writer physical separation OR vendor-SQLite swap). Pack\n  5 + Pack 6 + Pack 6.G falsified every canonical-SQLite lever\n  measurable on the AC-020 fixture.\n\n### `Engine.open` structured open report\n\nBoth Python and TypeScript SDKs currently return only the engine handle\nfrom `Engine.open`. The structured open report (migration-version-\nreached, embedder-identity-confirmed, open-stage data) defined in\n`design/engine.md` and called for by `interfaces/{python,typescript}.md`\nis populated on the native Rust side (`OpenedEngine.report`) but\n**dropped by both bindings in 0.6.0**.\n\nSurfacing the open report defers to **0.6.1** (slice\n`12-TX-OPENREPORT`). Symmetric across both bindings, so not a\nTS-vs-Python parity gap. Clients depending on open-report data\nshould pin to 0.6.1 when it ships.\n\n### Logical-id verbs\n\n`purge_logical_id` and `restore_logical_id` deferred to **0.7.x**\n(HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17 per Phase 12-V-VERBS decision). The\ncanonical-identity substrate (`row_id` / `logical_id` /\n`superseded_at` / `restore_provenance` columns, partial unique\nindex on `(logical_id, kind)`, writer supersession step) is\ndesign-only in 0.6.0 — verbs cannot be built without the substrate.\n\n**Client workaround for 0.6.0**: bulk-delete by source uses\n`fathomdb recover --excise-source <id>` (landed in Phase 10a).\nRestore-from-log workflows wait for 0.7.x.\n\nSee `dev/design/recovery.md` § Logical-id purge and restore for\nthe design + substrate spec.\n\n### TypeScript SDK parity\n\n- TS milestone 1 shipped 2026-04-07; not yet feature-equal with\n  Python. TS Python-parity is a Phase 12 deliverable (will close\n  before GA tag) but lands after performance + security + verb\n  decisions. Until then, prefer the Python SDK for production\n  pilots.\n\n### Compatibility\n\n- **No 0.5.x compatibility shims or migrations.** 0.6.0 is a\n  rewrite; clients on 0.5.x must follow a separate migration\n  guide (not provided in 0.6.0).\n\n## How to follow along\n\n- Plan + status: `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` § Path to\n  Client-Ready (0.6.0 GA).\n- Public interface specs (internal-facing):\n  `dev/interfaces/{rust,python,typescript,cli,wire}.md`.\n- Acceptance scoreboard: `dev/acceptance.md`.\n\nWhen 0.6.0 GA tags, this page will be replaced with the final\nrelease notes including install commands for all three registries.\n","numLines":138,"startLine":1,"totalLines":138}}}
dev/plans/runs/12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z.log:132:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013ZAKEi34ZLjwKxv79bEYtV","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Python Public Interface\n3\tdate: 2026-04-24\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Public Python surface for 0.6.0\n6\tblast_radius: src/python/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# Python Interface\n11\t\n12\tThis file owns Python-visible symbol spelling and attribute casing.\n13\tCross-binding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n14\t\n15\t## Runtime surface\n16\t\n17\tThe canonical runtime verbs available to Python callers are:\n18\t\n19\t- `Engine.open(...)`\n20\t- `engine.write(...)`\n21\t- `engine.search(...)`\n22\t- `engine.close()`\n23\t- `admin.configure(...)`\n24\t\n25\t`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\n26\towned by `design/engine.md`.\n27\t\n28\t> **0.6.0 caveat (2026-05-17, Phase 12-TX).** The PyO3 binding currently\n29\t> returns the engine handle only; the structured open report is dropped.\n30\t> Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report:\n31\t> OpenReport }` and the report is populated, but binding-side surfacing\n32\t> defers to 0.6.1 (slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT). Clients that need\n33\t> migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage\n34\t> data wait for 0.6.1.\n35\t\n36\t`Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` accepts the\n37\tengine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in snake_case:\n38\t\n39\t- `embedder_pool_size`\n40\t- `scheduler_runtime_threads`\n41\t- `provenance_row_cap`\n42\t- `embedder_call_timeout_ms`\n43\t- `slow_threshold_ms`\n44\t\n45\tThe keyword form and `EngineConfig` object form are equivalent. Python\n46\texecutor usage remains caller-owned and is not an engine config field.\n47\t\n48\t## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n49\t\n50\tThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n51\t\n52\t- `engine.drain(timeout_s=...)`\n53\t- `engine.counters()`\n54\t- `engine.set_profiling(enabled=...)`\n55\t- `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(value=...)`\n56\t\n57\tSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n58\t\n59\t- `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`\n60\t\n61\tThe helper maps engine events into Python `logging.LogRecord`s with the stable\n62\t`fathomdb` payload described by `design/bindings.md`.\n63\t\n64\t## Caller-visible data shapes\n65\t\n66\t- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n67\t- `SearchResult.projection_cursor`\n68\t- `SearchResult.soft_fallback.branch`\n69\t\n70\t`soft_fallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n71\t\n72\t## Errors\n73\t\n74\tPython exposes one catch-all base class plus one concrete subclass per canonical\n75\trow in `design/errors.md`.\n76\t\n77\tExamples of caller-visible subclasses:\n78\t\n79\t- `DatabaseLockedError`\n80\t- `CorruptionError`\n81\t- `MigrationError`\n82\t- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n83\t- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n84\t- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n85\t- `SchemaValidationError`\n86\t- `OverloadedError`\n87\t- `ClosingError`\n88\t\n89\tPayload fields remain typed attributes; callers do not dispatch on message\n90\ttext.\n91\t\n92\t## Non-presence\n93\t\n94\tPython does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\n95\tthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `check-integrity`, `--quick`,\n96\t`--full`, or `--round-trip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n97\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"5f49aef5-5cea-406d-8e6f-004a8be18267","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:21.070Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/dev/interfaces/python.md","content":"---\ntitle: Python Public Interface\ndate: 2026-04-24\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Public Python surface for 0.6.0\nblast_radius: src/python/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# Python Interface\n\nThis file owns Python-visible symbol spelling and attribute casing.\nCross-binding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Runtime surface\n\nThe canonical runtime verbs available to Python callers are:\n\n- `Engine.open(...)`\n- `engine.write(...)`\n- `engine.search(...)`\n- `engine.close()`\n- `admin.configure(...)`\n\n`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\nowned by `design/engine.md`.\n\n> **0.6.0 caveat (2026-05-17, Phase 12-TX).** The PyO3 binding currently\n> returns the engine handle only; the structured open report is dropped.\n> Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report:\n> OpenReport }` and the report is populated, but binding-side surfacing\n> defers to 0.6.1 (slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT). Clients that need\n> migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage\n> data wait for 0.6.1.\n\n`Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` accepts the\nengine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in snake_case:\n\n- `embedder_pool_size`\n- `scheduler_runtime_threads`\n- `provenance_row_cap`\n- `embedder_call_timeout_ms`\n- `slow_threshold_ms`\n\nThe keyword form and `EngineConfig` object form are equivalent. Python\nexecutor usage remains caller-owned and is not an engine config field.\n\n## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n\nThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n\n- `engine.drain(timeout_s=...)`\n- `engine.counters()`\n- `engine.set_profiling(enabled=...)`\n- `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(value=...)`\n\nSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n\n- `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`\n\nThe helper maps engine events into Python `logging.LogRecord`s with the stable\n`fathomdb` payload described by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Caller-visible data shapes\n\n- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n- `SearchResult.projection_cursor`\n- `SearchResult.soft_fallback.branch`\n\n`soft_fallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n\n## Errors\n\nPython exposes one catch-all base class plus one concrete subclass per canonical\nrow in `design/errors.md`.\n\nExamples of caller-visible subclasses:\n\n- `DatabaseLockedError`\n- `CorruptionError`\n- `MigrationError`\n- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n- `SchemaValidationError`\n- `OverloadedError`\n- `ClosingError`\n\nPayload fields remain typed attributes; callers do not dispatch on message\ntext.\n\n## Non-presence\n\nPython does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\nthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `check-integrity`, `--quick`,\n`--full`, or `--round-trip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n","numLines":97,"startLine":1,"totalLines":97}}}
dev/plans/runs/12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z.log:169:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BnFxNoENmQBYGtfWeALcQs","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: TypeScript Public Interface\n3\tdate: 2026-04-24\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Public TypeScript surface for 0.6.0\n6\tblast_radius: src/ts/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# TypeScript Interface\n11\t\n12\tThis file owns TypeScript-visible symbol spelling and export shape. Cross-\n13\tbinding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n14\t\n15\t## Runtime surface\n16\t\n17\tThe canonical runtime verbs available to TypeScript callers are:\n18\t\n19\t- `Engine.open(...)`\n20\t- `engine.write(...)`\n21\t- `engine.search(...)`\n22\t- `engine.close()`\n23\t- `admin.configure(...)`\n24\t\n25\tAll runtime operations are Promise-returning on the TS surface.\n26\t\n27\t`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\n28\towned by `design/engine.md`.\n29\t\n30\t> **0.6.0 caveat (2026-05-17, Phase 12-TX).** The napi-rs binding currently\n31\t> returns the engine handle only; the structured open report is dropped.\n32\t> Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report:\n33\t> OpenReport }` and the report is populated, but binding-side surfacing\n34\t> defers to 0.6.1 (slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT). Clients that need\n35\t> migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage\n36\t> data wait for 0.6.1.\n37\t\n38\t`Engine.open(path, options?)` accepts an options object with an `engineConfig`\n39\tmember carrying the engine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in camelCase:\n40\t\n41\t- `embedderPoolSize`\n42\t- `schedulerRuntimeThreads`\n43\t- `provenanceRowCap`\n44\t- `embedderCallTimeoutMs`\n45\t- `slowThresholdMs`\n46\t\n47\tIf TypeScript exposes ThreadsafeFunction handoff-pool sizing, that option is a\n48\tTS binding-runtime option beside `engineConfig`, not a canonical engine config\n49\tfield and not a Python parity obligation.\n50\t\n51\t## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n52\t\n53\tThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n54\t\n55\t- `engine.drain(timeoutMs)`\n56\t- `engine.counters()`\n57\t- `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`\n58\t- `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`\n59\t\n60\tSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n61\t\n62\t- `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })`\n63\t\n64\t`callback` receives the stable `fathomdb` payload described in\n65\t`design/bindings.md`.\n66\t\n67\t## Caller-visible data shapes\n68\t\n69\t- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n70\t- `SearchResult.projectionCursor`\n71\t- `SearchResult.softFallback.branch`\n72\t\n73\t`softFallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n74\t\n75\t## Errors\n76\t\n77\tTypeScript exposes one concrete leaf class per canonical row in\n78\t`design/errors.md`.\n79\t\n80\tLeaf-class examples:\n81\t\n82\t- `DatabaseLockedError`\n83\t- `CorruptionError`\n84\t- `MigrationError`\n85\t- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n86\t- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n87\t- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n88\t- `SchemaValidationError`\n89\t- `OverloadedError`\n90\t- `ClosingError`\n91\t\n92\tTypeScript exports one catch-all base class, `FathomDbError`, and every\n93\tconcrete leaf class in the `design/errors.md` matrix extends it. Open-time and\n94\truntime leaf classes remain distinct, but callers can catch `FathomDbError`\n95\tfor both.\n96\t\n97\t## Non-presence\n98\t\n99\tTypeScript does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\n100\tthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `checkIntegrity`, `quick`, `full`, or\n101\t`roundTrip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n102\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"0309b3df-6fb0-4112-bcbe-9c6cb2ec0104","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:29.385Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/dev/interfaces/typescript.md","content":"---\ntitle: TypeScript Public Interface\ndate: 2026-04-24\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Public TypeScript surface for 0.6.0\nblast_radius: src/ts/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# TypeScript Interface\n\nThis file owns TypeScript-visible symbol spelling and export shape. Cross-\nbinding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Runtime surface\n\nThe canonical runtime verbs available to TypeScript callers are:\n\n- `Engine.open(...)`\n- `engine.write(...)`\n- `engine.search(...)`\n- `engine.close()`\n- `admin.configure(...)`\n\nAll runtime operations are Promise-returning on the TS surface.\n\n`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\nowned by `design/engine.md`.\n\n> **0.6.0 caveat (2026-05-17, Phase 12-TX).** The napi-rs binding currently\n> returns the engine handle only; the structured open report is dropped.\n> Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report:\n> OpenReport }` and the report is populated, but binding-side surfacing\n> defers to 0.6.1 (slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT). Clients that need\n> migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage\n> data wait for 0.6.1.\n\n`Engine.open(path, options?)` accepts an options object with an `engineConfig`\nmember carrying the engine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in camelCase:\n\n- `embedderPoolSize`\n- `schedulerRuntimeThreads`\n- `provenanceRowCap`\n- `embedderCallTimeoutMs`\n- `slowThresholdMs`\n\nIf TypeScript exposes ThreadsafeFunction handoff-pool sizing, that option is a\nTS binding-runtime option beside `engineConfig`, not a canonical engine config\nfield and not a Python parity obligation.\n\n## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n\nThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n\n- `engine.drain(timeoutMs)`\n- `engine.counters()`\n- `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`\n- `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`\n\nSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n\n- `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })`\n\n`callback` receives the stable `fathomdb` payload described in\n`design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Caller-visible data shapes\n\n- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n- `SearchResult.projectionCursor`\n- `SearchResult.softFallback.branch`\n\n`softFallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n\n## Errors\n\nTypeScript exposes one concrete leaf class per canonical row in\n`design/errors.md`.\n\nLeaf-class examples:\n\n- `DatabaseLockedError`\n- `CorruptionError`\n- `MigrationError`\n- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n- `SchemaValidationError`\n- `OverloadedError`\n- `ClosingError`\n\nTypeScript exports one catch-all base class, `FathomDbError`, and every\nconcrete leaf class in the `design/errors.md` matrix extends it. Open-time and\nruntime leaf classes remain distinct, but callers can catch `FathomDbError`\nfor both.\n\n## Non-presence\n\nTypeScript does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\nthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `checkIntegrity`, `quick`, `full`, or\n`roundTrip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n","numLines":102,"startLine":1,"totalLines":102}}}
dev/plans/runs/12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z.log:187:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013knZs9MK8VFZ8WiLtqgY3j","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: TypeScript ↔ Python SDK Parity Matrix (12-TX)\n3\tdate: 2026-05-17\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Per-row mapping of Python public surface to TypeScript public surface; gap classification per `dev/design/bindings.md` § 1 \"surface-set parity invariant\"\n6\tblast_radius: src/python/fathomdb/; src/python/tests/; src/ts/src/; src/ts/tests/; src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs; src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs; src/python/fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi; dev/interfaces/python.md; dev/interfaces/typescript.md; dev/design/bindings.md; dev/design/errors.md\n7\tstatus: snapshot\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# 12-TX Parity Matrix\n11\t\n12\tSnapshot taken at slice start of Phase 12-TX (TS → Python parity audit).\n13\tPer `dev/design/bindings.md` § 1, the parity claim is \"same five-verb\n14\tcanonical set + same error class taxonomy + same data shapes in\n15\tlanguage-idiomatic spelling\". Cross-language idiom differences\n16\t(`camelCase` vs `snake_case`; positional vs kwarg; `Promise` vs sync;\n17\toptions-object vs keyword-arg) are **intentional per\n18\t`dev/interfaces/typescript.md` and `dev/interfaces/python.md`** and are\n19\trecorded here as `📋 divergence-by-design`, **not** as gaps.\n20\t\n21\tLegend:\n22\t\n23\t- ✅ **parity-OK** — both surfaces present; spec-compliant idiom differences acknowledged\n24\t- ❌ **gap** — TS missing what Python has, or vice versa, where the locked interface spec implies parity\n25\t- 📋 **divergence-by-design** — locked spec explicitly diverges\n26\t\n27\t## 1. Five-verb canonical surface (REQ-053; AC-057a)\n28\t\n29\t| Verb              | Python (`src/python/fathomdb/`)                                          | TypeScript (`src/ts/src/`)                                                                    | Status |\n30\t| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------ |\n31\t| `Engine.open`     | `Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` → `Engine`          | `Engine.open(path, options?)` → `Promise<Engine>`                                             | 📋 sync vs Promise; kwargs vs options-object; both per spec |\n32\t| `Engine.open` return: **structured open report** | NOT returned (PyO3 binding drops `OpenedEngine.report`) | NOT returned (napi binding drops `OpenedEngine.report`) | ⚠️ **0.6.0 documented gap** — locked specs (interfaces/python.md L25-28, interfaces/typescript.md L27-29) call for \"engine handle plus structured open report owned by design/engine.md\". Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report: OpenReport }` (engine src L541-553), but both bindings currently surface only the engine. Symmetric parity (both bindings drop it); not a TS-vs-Python gap. **Resolution:** implementation deferred to **0.6.1** as a follow-up slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT. Release notes disclose the gap; clients depending on migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage report wait for 0.6.1. Spec text in interfaces/{python,typescript}.md amended to add \"0.6.0 caveat\" note. |\n33\t| `engine.write`    | `engine.write(batch=None)` → `WriteReceipt` (sync)                       | `engine.write(batch=[])` → `Promise<WriteReceipt>`                                            | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec |\n34\t| `engine.search`   | `engine.search(query)` → `SearchResult` (sync)                           | `engine.search(query)` → `Promise<SearchResult>`                                              | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec |\n35\t| `engine.close`    | `engine.close()` → `None` (sync)                                         | `engine.close()` → `Promise<void>`                                                            | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec |\n36\t| `admin.configure` | `admin.configure(engine, *, name, body)` → `WriteReceipt` (module-level) | `admin.configure(engine, { name, body })` → `Promise<WriteReceipt>` (object-literal namespace) | ✅    |\n37\t\n38\t## 2. Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n39\t\n40\t| Method                       | Python                                                                      | TypeScript                                                  | Status |\n41\t| ---------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ------ |\n42\t| `drain`                      | `engine.drain(*, timeout_s: float\\|int = 0)` (sync)                          | `engine.drain(timeoutMs: number)` → `Promise<void>`         | 📋 timeout unit (seconds vs ms) + sync vs Promise per spec |\n43\t| `counters`                   | `engine.counters()` → `CounterSnapshot` (empty dataclass; **drops** native fields) | `engine.counters()` → `CounterSnapshot` (6 fields populated) | ❌ **gap closed in 12-TX**: Python wrapper threw away the 6 fields the PyO3 layer already returns |\n44\t| `set_profiling`              | `engine.set_profiling(*, enabled)`                                          | `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`                              | 📋 kwarg vs positional per spec |\n45\t| `set_slow_threshold_ms`      | `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(*, value)`                                    | `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`                          | 📋 kwarg vs positional per spec |\n46\t| Subscriber attach            | `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`   | `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })` | 📋 logging.Logger vs callback per `interfaces/python.md` § 51 + `interfaces/typescript.md` § 54 (explicitly different host-adapter shapes) |\n47\t\n48\t## 3. Caller-visible data shapes\n49\t\n50\t| Shape                | Python field set                                                                                                              | TypeScript field set                                                                                                                                       | Status |\n51\t| -------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------ |\n52\t| `WriteReceipt`       | `cursor: int`                                                                                                                 | `cursor: number`                                                                                                                                           | ✅    |\n53\t| `SoftFallback`       | `branch: Literal[\"vector\",\"text\"]`                                                                                            | `branch: \"vector\" \\| \"text\"`                                                                                                                              | ✅    |\n54\t| `SearchResult`       | `projection_cursor: int`, `soft_fallback: SoftFallback \\| None`, `results: list[str]`                                          | `projectionCursor: number`, `softFallback: SoftFallback \\| null`, `results: string[]`                                                                     | ✅ (casing) |\n55\t| `CounterSnapshot`    | _(was: empty dataclass)_; **after 12-TX**: `queries`, `writes`, `write_rows`, `admin_ops`, `cache_hit`, `cache_miss` (all `int`) | `queries`, `writes`, `writeRows`, `adminOps`, `cacheHit`, `cacheMiss` (all `number`)                                                                       | ❌ → ✅ (gap closed; 6 fields added to Python dataclass + wired through `Engine.counters`) |\n56\t| `EngineConfig`       | `embedder_pool_size`, `scheduler_runtime_threads`, `provenance_row_cap`, `embedder_call_timeout_ms`, `slow_threshold_ms` (all `int \\| None`) | same five knobs, `Optional<number>`, camelCase                                                                                                            | ✅    |\n57\t\n58\t## 4. Error-class taxonomy (15+ leaves per `dev/design/errors.md`)\n59\t\n60\tPython defines a root `EngineError` plus 18 concrete leaves. TypeScript\n61\tdefines `FathomDbError` plus 18 concrete leaves. Both bindings expose\n62\t1:1 the same leaf set:\n63\t\n64\t| Class                              | Python `errors.py` | TS `errors.ts` |\n65\t| ---------------------------------- | ------------------ | -------------- |\n66\t| (root)                             | `EngineError`      | `FathomDbError`|\n67\t| `StorageError`                     | ✅                | ✅            |\n68\t| `ProjectionError`                  | ✅                | ✅            |\n69\t| `VectorError`                      | ✅                | ✅            |\n70\t| `EmbedderError`                    | ✅                | ✅            |\n71\t| `EmbedderNotConfiguredError`       | ✅                | ✅            |\n72\t| `KindNotVectorIndexedError`        | ✅                | ✅            |\n73\t| `SchedulerError`                   | ✅                | ✅            |\n74\t| `OpStoreError`                     | ✅                | ✅            |\n75\t| `WriteValidationError`             | ✅                | ✅            |\n76\t| `SchemaValidationError`            | ✅                | ✅            |\n77\t| `OverloadedError`                  | ✅                | ✅            |\n78\t| `ClosingError`                     | ✅                | ✅            |\n79\t| `DatabaseLockedError`              | ✅ + `holder_pid` | ✅ + `holderPid` |\n80\t| `CorruptionError`                  | ✅ + `kind` / `stage` / `recovery_hint_code` / `doc_anchor` | ✅ + `kind` / `stage` / `recoveryHintCode` / `docAnchor` |\n81\t| `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`   | ✅                | ✅            |\n82\t| `MigrationError`                   | ✅                | ✅            |\n83\t| `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`    | ✅ + `stored_name` / `stored_revision` / `supplied_name` / `supplied_revision` | ✅ + camelCase counterparts |\n84\t| `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`   | ✅ + `stored` / `supplied` | ✅ + `stored` / `supplied` |\n85\t| Panic carrier (contract bug; not a `FathomDbError` subclass) | `pyo3_runtime.PanicException` (PyO3-owned, not `EngineError`) | `FathomDbPanicError` (TS-owned; not `FathomDbError`) | ✅ both deliberately outside the catch-all root |\n86\t\n87\t**Status: parity-OK after 12-TX.** No new TS leaves required.\n88\t\n89\t## 5. Type-stub completeness\n90\t\n91\t| Native member                                | Python `_fathomdb.pyi` | TS `binding.ts` `NativeEngine` / `NativeModule` |\n92\t| -------------------------------------------- | ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |\n93\t| `Engine.open`                                | ✅                    | ✅                                             |\n94\t| `Engine.write` / `search` / `close` / `drain` / `counters` / `set_profiling` / `set_slow_threshold_ms` | ✅                    | ✅                                             |\n95\t| `Engine.attach_logging_subscriber` (Python) / `attachSubscriber` (TS) | ✅                    | ✅                                             |\n96\t| `admin_configure` / `adminConfigure`         | ✅                    | ✅                                             |\n97\t| `force_panic_for_test` / `forcePanicForTest` | ✅                    | ✅                                             |\n98\t| `force_panic_in_accessor_for_test` (TS-only AC-067 sync-path probe) | n/a | ✅ |\n99\t\n100\t`forcePanicInAccessorForTest` is a TS-binding-specific probe (no\n101\tPython counterpart): per `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs:707`,\n102\tit exists to assert sync `#[napi]` accessor panic translation, which\n103\thas no analogue in PyO3 (Python is sync-only; there is no async/sync\n104\tsplit). 📋 divergence-by-design.\n105\t\n106\tAll 18 leaf classes appear in both stubs.\n107\t\n108\t## 6. Test counterparts\n109\t\n110\t| Python file                       | TS file                                | Status |\n111\t| --------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | ------ |\n112\t| `tests/conftest.py`               | `tests/helpers.ts`                     | ✅ |\n113\t| `tests/test_errors.py`            | `tests/errors.test.ts`                 | ✅ (after 12-TX adds `EmbedderNotConfiguredError` + `KindNotVectorIndexedError` to Python `LEAF_CLASSES` to match TS coverage) |\n114\t| `tests/test_typed_errors.py`      | `tests/typed-errors.test.ts`           | ✅ |\n115\t| `tests/test_ffi_safety.py`        | `tests/ffi-safety.test.ts`             | ✅ |\n116\t| `tests/test_no_recovery_surface.py` | `tests/no-recovery-surface.test.ts`  | ✅ |\n117\t| `tests/test_save_time_validation.py` | `tests/save-time-validation.test.ts` | ✅ |\n118\t| `tests/test_surface.py`           | `tests/surface.test.ts`                | ✅ |\n119\t| `tests/test_scaffold.py`          | `tests/scaffold.test.ts` _(added in 12-TX; cursor-advances-on-write)_ | ❌ → ✅ |\n120\t| `tests/test_property_template.py` | _(none; hypothesis-based placeholder)_ | 📋 divergence-by-design: Python file is a hypothesis scaffold (`assert x == x`) explicitly marked \"Replace this trivial property when real Python API surface lands\". No real invariant is tested; replicating into TS adds a fast-check dependency for an equally trivial placeholder. Net-negative LoC: defer the TS port until either side gets a real property test, at which point both ports land together. |\n121\t\n122\t## 7. Out-of-scope idiom translation (locked per spec)\n123\t\n124\tThe following patterns are **not